Interface EvictableStore<A,E extends Evictable>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - Type of the accessor (id) of the EvictionCandidate
    E - Type of the Evictable value of EvictionCandidate
    All Known Subinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CacheRecordHashMap, HeapNearCacheRecordMap, QueryCacheRecordHashMap

    public interface EvictableStore<A,E extends Evictable>
    Interface for store implementations that holds Evictable entries to evict.

    • Method Detail

      • tryEvict

        <C extends EvictionCandidate<A,E>> boolean tryEvict(C evictionCandidate,
                                                    EvictionListener<A,E> evictionListener)
        The evict method is called by the EvictionStrategy to eventually evict, by the policy, selected candidate from the internal data structures. It could be the selected evicted candidate cannot be evicted. For example it might be gone at the time when the method is executed. In this case it will indicate this condition by returning false.
        Parameters:
        evictionCandidate - EvictionCandidate to be evicted
        evictionListener - EvictionListener to listen evicted entries
        Returns:
        true if the candidate was evicted, otherwise returns false
